      "description": "Older fair-condition example that presents as a usable driver, but not a show car. It has the kind of cosmetic wear, aging, and imperfections you\u2019d expect from a vehicle that has been used and not fully restored, and it should appeal most to someone looking for an affordable entry point rather than a perfect example. Expect visible wear inside and out, and plan on addressing some maintenance or smaller issues over time to bring it up to a higher standard. Honest car for someone who understands what a fair-condition driver is and wants something they can use, improve, and enjoy as they go.",
